The deceased landed in front of a truck earlier this afternoon on the highway heading towards Paarl. CAPE TOWN - A man has died after jumping off the Okavango bridge onto the N1 in Cape Town.The deceased landed in front of a truck earlier this afternoon on the highway heading towards Paarl.Western Cape Traffic Chief Kenny Africa said: Currently we have a situation on the N1 outgoing at Okavango, where a person jumped off the bridge and landed in front of a truck. That part of the N1 has been closed to traffic. (Winnie Theletsane)